               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa ʾaślәṭi, Lectionary for the week (fols. 4ra-28rb) &#xD;
II) Barәkännä ʾәgziʾo… “Bless us, O Lord…” (Blessing prayer) (fols. 28rb-29va)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The work (Texts I-II) is called Maṣḥafa ʾaslǝṭ in the colophon (fol.
                        9ra).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        f.
                        39vb: ዝመጽፍ[sic]፡ አስልጥ፡ ዘ፯ቱ፡ ዕለት፡ ዘአባ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወአቡሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወአሙ፡ ወለተ፡
                        ብርሃን፡ ዘአጥረያ፡ ንዋዩ[sic]፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፸ወ፪ቱ፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡
                        በዘመነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ተጽሐፈ።
                        The colophon mentions that the Ms. is in the possession of (but
                           appareantly meaning: commissioned by) Takla Hāymānot, was written in 1972
                           A.M. (= 1979-80 A.D.). The relatives of Takla Hāymānot(his father
                           Yoḥannǝs and his mother Walatta Bǝrhān) are also mentioned.
                     </colophon>
               </msContents>
